fm: ListNode *rotateRight(ListNode *head, int k) {         if (head == NULL || k == 0) return head;         int len = 1;         ListNode* p = head, *pre;         while (p->next != NULL)         {             p = p->next;             len++;         }         k = len - k % len;         p->next = head;         int step = 0;         while (step < k)         {             p = p->next;             step++;         }         head = p->next;         p->next = NULL;         return head;     }

fm: bool searchMatrix(vector<vector<int> > &matrix, int target) {         int row = matrix.size();         if (row == 0) return false;         int col = matrix[0].size();         if (target < matrix[0][0]) return false;         int start = 0, end = row - 1;          while (start <= end)         {             int mid = (start + end) / 2;             if (matrix[mid][0] == target) return true;              if (matrix[mid][0] < target) start = mid + 1;             else end = mid - 1;         }          int searchRow = end;          start = 0, end = col - 1;         while (start <= end)         {             int mid = (start + end) / 2;             if (matrix[searchRow][mid] == target) return true;              if (matrix[searchRow][mid] < target) start = mid + 1;             else end = mid - 1;         }         return false;     }

fm: vector<int> searchRange(vector<int>& A, int target) {         int n = A.size();         vector<int> result;         result.push_back(-1);         result.push_back(-1);         // find the low bound of the range, O(lgn)         int start = 0, end = n - 1;         while (start < end)         {             int mid = (start + end) / 2;             if (A[mid] < target)             {                 start = mid + 1;                 continue;             }             end = mid;         }         int low_bound = A[start] == target ? start : -1;         if (low_bound == -1)         {             return result;         }         // find the high bound of the range, O(lgn)         start = low_bound, end = n;         while (start < end)         {             int mid = (start + end) / 2;             if (A[mid] > target)             {                 end = mid;                 continue;             }             start = mid + 1;         }         int high_bound = start - 1;         result.clear();         result.push_back(low_bound);         result.push_back(high_bound);         return result;     }

fm: int searchInsert(vector<int>& A, int target) {         int l = 0, r = A.size() - 1;         while (l <= r)         {             int mid = (l + r) / 2;             if (A[mid] == target) return mid;             if (mid > l && A[mid] > target && A[mid - 1] < target )                 return mid;             if (A[mid] > target)                 r = mid - 1;             else                 l = mid + 1;         }         return l;     }

fm: int search(vector<int>& A, int target) {         int l = 0, r = A.size() - 1;         while (l <= r)         {             int m = (l + r) / 2;             if (A[m] == target) return m;             if (A[m] >= A[l])             {                 // target 5 in {4,5,6,2,3}                 if (A[l] <= target && target <= A[m])                     r = m - 1;                 else                     l = m + 1;             }             else             {                 // target 2 in {5,0,1,2,3}                 if (A[m] < target && target < A[l])                     l = m + 1;                 else                     r = m - 1;             }         }         return -1;     }

fm: bool search(vector<int>& A, int target) {         int start = 0;         int end = A.size() - 1;         while (start <= end)         {             int mid = (start + end) / 2;             if (A[mid] == target) return true;             if (A[start] < A[mid])             {                 if (target >= A[start] && target < A[mid])                     end = mid - 1;                 else                     start = mid + 1;             }             else if (A[start] > A[mid])             {                 if (target > A[mid] && target <= A[end])                     start = mid + 1;                 else                     end = mid - 1;             }             else //skip duplicate one, A[start] == A[mid]                 start++;         }         return false;     }

fm: void setZeroes(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {         assert(matrix.size() > 0);         int row = matrix.size(), col = matrix[0].size();         bool zerorow = false, zerocol = false;         for (int i = 0; i < col; i++)             if (matrix[0][i] == 0)                 zerorow = 1;         for (int i = 0; i < row; i++)             if (matrix[i][0] == 0)                 zerocol = 1;         for (int i = 1; i < row; i++)             for (int j = 1; j < col; j++)                 if (matrix[i][j] == 0)                 {                     matrix[0][j] = 0;                     matrix[i][0] = 0;                 }         for (int i = 1; i < row; i++)             for (int j = 1; j < col; j++)                 if (matrix[i][0] == 0 || matrix[0][j] == 0)                     matrix[i][j] = 0;         if (zerorow == 1)             for (int i = 0; i < col; i++)                 matrix[0][i] = 0;         if (zerocol == 1)             for (int i = 0; i < row; i++)                 matrix[i][0] = 0;     }

fm: string simplifyPath(string path) {         vector<string> stack;         assert(path[0] == '/');         int i = 0;         while (i < path.size())         {             //skip the begining '////'             while (path[i] == '/' && i < path.size()) i++;             if (i == path.size())                 break;             int start = i;             //decide the end boundary             while (path[i] != '/' && i < path.size()) i++;             int end = i - 1;             string element = path.substr(start, end - start + 1);             if (element == "..")             {                 if (stack.size() > 0)                     stack.pop_back();             }             else if (element != ".")                 stack.push_back(element);         }         if (stack.size() == 0) return "/";         string simpPath;         for (int i = 0; i < stack.size(); i++)             simpPath += "/" + stack[i];         return simpPath;     }

fm: int singleNumber(int A[], int n) {         int left = A[0];         for (int i = 1; i < n; i++)         {             left = left ^ A[i];         }         return left;     }
